Topics.name: CSS
Topics.desc: CSS is a programming language used for styling web pages.It allows developers to separate the presentation of a webpage from its content, making it easier to maintain and update the styling of a website.

Topics.name: SQL
Topics.desc: SQL is a language for managing and manipulating databases. Key commands include SELECT (retrieve), INSERT (add), UPDATE (modify), DELETE (remove), JOIN (combine), WHERE (filter), GROUP BY (group), and ORDER BY (sort).

Topics.name: Angular
Topics.desc: Angular is an open-source web application framework developed by Google for building complex and dynamic web applications using TypeScript. It provides features such as two-way data binding.
